          }\\n                return loadedClass;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        private static boolean shouldLoadChildFirst(String name) {\\n            return name.equals(IsolatedAction.class.getName())\\n                    || name.equals(NonLogChute.class.getName())\\n                    || name.startsWith(\\\"io.sundr.deps.\\\");\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780740017969}}\n19991:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating class naming rules**\\n\\nI need to check whether we should avoid using \\\"$\\\" in test class or file names. We did use a string like \\\"$IsolatedAction,\\\" but the existing codes generated it too. The instruction says never to use \\\"$\\\" in class names, but it seems it might not apply to file names. It gets tricky because we have an inner class named `IsolatedAction`, which does include \\\"$\\\". However, using `IsolatedAction.class.getName()` might return a string without the \\\"$\\\" for outer class names. It's also important we don't skip Native with early returns, as that can catch errors. I'll need to figure this out!\\n\\n**Analyzing NativeImageSupport implications**\\n\\nI think there's a potential issue with the `NativeImageSupport` import, which seems to stem from the plugin dependency. There's also the `Class.forName` direct use in the test that could lead to dynamic access issues, which might be okay. This test will probably run in a native image after compilation, but I worry about the `URLClassLoader` returning only parent classes. \\n\\nIn native images, codeSource URLs could be null for classes, raising more complexity. Existing code checks the codeSource URL before a certain condition, which adds a layer of uncertainty. Ultimately, I need to determine how best to manage this situation to avoid failures!\\n\\n**Considering dynamic class loading issues**\\n\\nI'm pondering whet